    "narrative": "For the April 11th slate, the Austin Waves offense is anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (80.85) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10), both of whom benefit from highly favorable matchups against Jack Leiter and Ryan Feltner, respectively. **Kyle Tucker** is our premier start, bolstered by strong xwOBA metrics and wind conditions that favor an aggressive approach. Similarly, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a high-upside matchup against a weak opposing starter, and his speed profile is weaponized by a slow delivery from the pitcher, maximizing his chances of securing the stolen bases we so desperately need. **Gunnar Henderson** (70.88) rounds out the top tier, as his elite spot at the top of the order and a park factor boost outweigh the inherent risk of facing a polished arm like Logan Webb.\n\nWe are hunting platoon advantages across the board, most notably with **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.04), whose score is significantly elevated by a strong dynamic platoon edge against J. Lopez. While **Nolan Schanuel** (64.13) carries a lower base, the matchup against Williamson provides a +18% lift in SP skill efficiency, making him a reliable play. The most difficult decision today was leaving **Marcell Ozuna** (52.05) on the bench. Despite a solid park factor and a decent matchup against E. Cabrera, the optimizer favored the higher efficiency floors provided by the rest of the utility and corner infield group, specifically forcing **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.92) into the lineup based on his superior xwOBA potential, even though he faces a tougher test in Ryan.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the current number of \"Lineup Pending\" designations. We are operating under the assumption that **Gunnar Henderson**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Jackson Merrill** retain their projected spots; any late shifts in order could dampen their efficiency scores. While we are confident in the projected production, keep a close eye on the catchers, **Liam Hicks** and **Drake Baldwin**, whose scores are hovering near the marginal threshold; should weather patterns shift or lineup cards reveal a defensive substitution, we are prepared to pivot to protect our game caps.",
